	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=427265"><span id="Scholar">RattailScoundral</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">42 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p> Guess it's all a matter of perspective, but I'd put the horn in your primary and RB in secondary. The horn is a much faster weapon allowing duel wield to work more often. The horn also has a better ratio making for better DPS than the other way around, even if only a slight differance. Typically you want your fast weapon in PRI and power weapon in SEC, gives you the best duel-wield DPS.<br/><br/> Backstabs are supposedly more powerful with the power weapon in primary, but seeing as you'll only get about 1 BS per 10 normal attacks with the horn, your backstab would have to do 10x the damage of a regular attack to balance it out. I know at level 41 my horn is doing about 20-40 damage per hit and backstabs for around 170, so I'd prefer faster attacks to stronger backstabs. The ratios are nearly identical though.<br/><br/> My suggestion: Horn in PRI, Ragebringer in SEC<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Oct 26 01:19:10 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
